3
00:00:18,119 --> 00:00:21,055
Nowhere else in the world

4
00:00:21,122 --> 00:00:31,065
♪～

5
00:00:31,132 --> 00:00:35,569
(Minseok) 《If it's nowhere...》

6
00:00:35,636 --> 00:00:37,638
《I was thinking》

7
00:00:44,512 --> 00:00:47,448
>> Korean

8
00:00:47,515 --> 00:00:55,055
(applause)

9
00:00:56,524 --> 00:01:04,899
Korean

10
00:01:04,965 --> 00:01:07,835
(applause)

11
00:01:08,335 --> 00:01:42,203
Korean

12
00:01:44,839 --> 00:01:48,242
(Jung Hoon) [This is your place from now on]

13
00:01:51,278 --> 00:01:58,786
Korean

14
00:02:00,354 --> 00:02:07,228
Korean

15
00:02:07,795 --> 00:02:17,304
(applause)

16
00:02:17,838 --> 00:02:23,878
Korean

17
00:02:23,944 --> 00:02:25,946
(Jung Hoon) Uh...

18
00:02:29,450 --> 00:02:31,952
(Jung Hoon) Uh...

19
00:02:36,457 --> 00:02:39,393
(Eri) Hurry up and get an ambulance. Yes.

20
00:02:39,460 --> 00:02:41,962
Korean

21
00:02:50,971 --> 00:02:55,976
(Jung Hoon) [This is your place from now on]

22
00:03:02,483 --> 00:03:04,418
[Kenchana? ]

23
00:03:06,420 --> 00:03:08,355
Are you okay?

24
00:03:08,422 --> 00:03:30,945
♪～

25
00:03:40,955 --> 00:03:44,458
Ah... Ugh...｡

26
00:04:10,417 --> 00:04:13,854
(footsteps)

27
00:04:13,921 --> 00:04:16,757
(Kyunhua) Hahaha…｡

28
00:04:17,424 --> 00:04:25,933
Korean

29
00:05:50,951 --> 00:05:52,953
Get out!

30
00:06:00,961 --> 00:06:02,396
(knock)

31
00:06:02,463 --> 00:06:04,398
(sound of door opening)

32
00:06:11,405 --> 00:06:12,906
Korean

33
00:07:06,460 --> 00:07:17,971
♪～

34
00:08:49,997 --> 00:08:51,498
\Wow! /

35
00:09:00,007 --> 00:09:01,942
(Momoko) Okay, then open your mouth.

36
00:09:02,009 --> 00:09:03,877
Ah~｡ (Ellie) Ah~｡

37
00:09:03,944 --> 00:09:06,380
(Momoko) Yeah, it's okay, it's just a cold.

38
00:09:06,446 --> 00:09:08,382
(Chloe) Good. (Momoko) Ellie.

39
00:09:08,448 --> 00:09:10,384
If you take your medicine properly, you'll feel better.

40
00:09:10,450 --> 00:09:12,386
(Ellie) Yeah. (Momoko) Yeah.

41
00:09:12,452 --> 00:09:14,388
>> Thank you. (Momoko) Yes, please don't get cold →

42
00:09:14,454 --> 00:09:16,390
Please warm it up properly. >> Yes.

43
00:09:16,456 --> 00:09:18,392
(Momoko) Oh, and some nutritious food that is easy to digest→

44
00:09:18,458 --> 00:09:20,394
After feeding them a lot...

45
00:09:20,460 --> 00:09:22,396
(Mika) Yes, that's it! Ah, please take care of yourself.

46
00:09:22,462 --> 00:09:24,398
(Chloe) Thank you very much. (Momoko) Ah...｡

47
00:09:24,464 --> 00:09:26,900
>> Momo-chan-sensei, the next person can come in.

48
00:09:26,967 --> 00:09:28,902
(Momoko) Ah, mom. (Mika) Hey!

49
00:09:28,969 --> 00:09:31,405
(Momoko) If he seems to be getting feverish again, please be sure to bring him.

50
00:09:31,471 --> 00:09:33,907
>> Teacher, I'll go. (Momoko) Take care.

51
00:09:33,974 --> 00:09:35,909
Yes, yes… >> Already!

52
00:09:35,976 --> 00:09:38,412
Momo-chan-sensei, if we keep going at this pace, we'll never finish.

53
00:09:38,478 --> 00:09:40,914
Today, the director will be visiting patients all day.

54
00:09:40,981 --> 00:09:42,916
(Momoko) I'm sorry.

55
00:09:42,983 --> 00:09:46,420
>> I'm always sorry, teacher.

56
00:09:46,486 --> 00:09:49,923
(Kazami) Carpentry is my specialty.

57
00:09:49,990 --> 00:09:52,492
I'm better than the doctor.

58
00:09:53,994 --> 00:09:55,929
Ah, it hurts!

59
00:09:55,996 --> 00:09:58,932
Anyway, the director sells oil in various places...

60
00:09:58,999 --> 00:10:01,435
Huh? Oh, what are you doing?

61
00:10:01,501 --> 00:10:03,937
I'll admit the next patient. (Momoko) Hey, Takuto.

62
00:10:04,004 --> 00:10:05,939
📱(Speaker: Momoko) You're bored, right? Come right away.

63
00:10:06,006 --> 00:10:10,944
(Takuto) You see, I don't have the word ``free time'' in my dictionary.

64
00:10:11,011 --> 00:10:13,947
(Momoko) Anyway, please come right away. There are a lot of patients today.

65
00:10:14,014 --> 00:10:15,949
(Staff) Mr. Yamashiro, please.

66
00:10:16,016 --> 00:10:17,517
(Takuto) Yes.

67
00:10:21,521 --> 00:10:23,957
(Takuto) That's too bad, Momoko.

68
00:10:24,024 --> 00:10:26,460
Because everyone is waiting for me.

69
00:10:26,526 --> 00:10:28,996
📱 Ah, wait, Takuto, Takuto...｡

70
00:10:29,229 --> 00:10:30,430
(Ralph) Well, today.

71
00:10:30,530 --> 00:10:32,399
We had a wonderful guest come to visit us.

72
00:10:33,333 --> 00:10:37,771
This is Takuto Yamashiro, the vice president of Yamashiro Memorial Hospital!

73
00:10:37,838 --> 00:10:40,340
(Takuto) Hello everyone.

74
00:10:42,843 --> 00:10:46,279
(Mika) It's crazy, it's trending.

75
00:10:46,346 --> 00:10:48,782
(Momoko) Ah... you idiot.

76
00:10:48,849 --> 00:10:51,284
I was an idiot for trying to rely on him.

77
00:10:51,351 --> 00:10:55,288
Anyway, we have no choice but to get through today.

78
00:10:55,355 --> 00:10:56,857
>> Yes!

79
00:11:03,797 --> 00:11:07,300
(Momoko) Ah... it's finally over.

80
00:11:10,303 --> 00:11:12,739
(Momoko) Hmm!

81
00:11:12,806 --> 00:11:17,244
Ah! Thank you for your hard work.

82
00:11:17,310 --> 00:11:19,246
(Sound of a gust of wind) (Momoko) Ow!

83
00:11:19,312 --> 00:11:21,248
(Sound of gust of wind)

84
00:11:21,314 --> 00:11:23,316
(Momoko) Hmm.

85
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:28,755
>> Korean

86
00:11:28,822 --> 00:11:30,323
(Jehyon) Ah!

87
00:11:37,330 --> 00:11:39,266
(Momoko) Are you okay?

88
00:11:39,332 --> 00:11:41,334
(Minseok) Please help me.

89
00:11:43,336 --> 00:11:47,340
Help this person.

90
00:11:49,342 --> 00:11:50,777
(Momoko) Yes.

91
00:11:50,844 --> 00:11:52,779
I'll take this one.

92
00:11:52,846 --> 00:11:55,282
It's okay to take it slow. Take it slow. (Jehyun) Ah...

93
00:11:55,348 --> 00:11:56,783
Korean

94
00:11:56,850 --> 00:11:59,786
(Momoko) That's good. (Jehyun) Ah...｡

95
00:12:17,337 --> 00:12:18,271
(Momoko) I'll move it.

96
00:12:18,605 --> 00:12:20,273
>> It will hurt a little, but please be patient.

97
00:12:20,874 --> 00:12:23,810
Korean

98
00:12:23,877 --> 00:12:26,813
(Jehyun) Ah... ah...｡

99
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:28,315
(Momoko) Almost there.

100
00:12:28,381 --> 00:12:29,883
>> Korean

101
00:12:30,884 --> 00:12:33,320
(stomach growling)

102
00:12:33,386 --> 00:12:35,822
Erm...

103
00:12:35,889 --> 00:12:38,325
I don't have time to eat rice.

104
00:12:38,391 --> 00:12:40,327
>> Korean

105
00:12:40,393 --> 00:12:42,829
(Momoko) You don't need an interpreter for that!

106
00:12:42,896 --> 00:12:45,332
>> Korean

107
00:12:45,398 --> 00:12:47,334
(Momoko) Please stop it hahaha...｡

108
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:49,402
(Minseok) Sorry. (Jaehyun) Hahaha…｡

109
00:12:52,405 --> 00:12:54,841
(Minseok) All other hospitals are full.

110
00:12:54,908 --> 00:12:56,843
Thank you very much.

111
00:12:56,910 --> 00:12:59,846
(Momoko) No, then take care.

112
00:12:59,913 --> 00:13:01,915
Excuse me.

113
00:13:09,356 --> 00:13:11,291
(Momoko) I'll touch it.

114
00:13:11,358 --> 00:13:12,859
(Minseok) Ah.

115
00:13:15,362 --> 00:13:17,797
(Momoko) You can't afford to get injured like this.

116
00:13:17,864 --> 00:13:20,801
There may be lifelong aftereffects.

117
00:13:20,867 --> 00:13:23,870
What happened?

118
00:13:27,874 --> 00:13:29,876
(Jeheon) [Wow! ]

119
00:13:32,879 --> 00:13:36,316
[Ah...! ]

120
00:13:36,383 --> 00:13:38,318
[Ah...]

121
00:13:38,385 --> 00:13:39,819
(Minseok) [Are you okay? ]

122
00:13:39,886 --> 00:13:44,825
>> Korean

123
00:13:44,891 --> 00:13:48,328
(Momoko) Is that so crazy? Because he's not an action star.

124
00:13:48,395 --> 00:13:49,830
(Minseok) Sorry.

125
00:13:49,896 --> 00:13:52,332
(Momoko) Are you from the hotel right over there?

126
00:13:52,399 --> 00:13:56,336
(Minseok) Yes, I started my new post today.

127
00:13:56,403 --> 00:14:00,840
(Momoko) Even if you're at work, if you feel pain, please tell me.

128
00:14:00,907 --> 00:14:04,344
It's my job to fix that.

129
00:14:05,845 --> 00:14:07,847
It hurts, right?

130
00:14:10,850 --> 00:14:13,353
(Minseok) Ah, no, it's okay.

131
00:14:14,854 --> 00:14:18,792
(Momoko) Don't force yourself to laugh and pretend to be fine.

132
00:14:18,859 --> 00:14:24,364
If you do that, your heart will hurt.

133
00:14:28,868 --> 00:14:34,374
>> Korean

134
00:14:42,883 --> 00:14:44,884
(Minseok) Please. (Driver) Yes.

135
00:14:53,393 --> 00:14:55,328
(Stomach growling sound) (Keyboard typing sound)

136
00:14:55,395 --> 00:14:57,330
(Momoko) Ah, a little more, a little more.

137
00:14:57,397 --> 00:14:59,332
>> Mr. Momo-chan, this is a gift.

138
00:14:59,399 --> 00:15:01,334
(Momoko) Huh! >> The patient from earlier thanked me.

139
00:15:01,401 --> 00:15:02,769
(Momoko) Huh?

140
00:15:02,836 --> 00:15:14,281
♪～

141
00:15:14,347 --> 00:15:17,784
(Momoko) I wonder if people thought I was a big glutton?

142
00:15:17,851 --> 00:15:19,853
I'll enjoy having this.

143
00:15:21,354 --> 00:15:24,291
Hmm! delicious!

144
00:15:24,357 --> 00:15:51,885
♪～

145
00:16:00,126 --> 00:16:04,564
(Min-seok) My name is Kim Min-seok and I have been appointed as the deputy manager.

146
00:16:04,631 --> 00:16:09,069
I can speak Japanese, so please feel free to talk to me.

147
00:16:09,135 --> 00:16:13,073
Thank you for your continued support starting today.

148
00:16:13,139 --> 00:16:16,076
>> At the head office in Korea... >> That's the heir of the example...

149
00:16:16,142 --> 00:16:18,578
What did you do...

150
00:16:18,645 --> 00:16:22,582
(Mizushima) He came to this hotel on an unusual personnel basis.

151
00:16:22,649 --> 00:16:25,085
Hurry up, this suite room.

152
00:16:25,151 --> 00:16:29,089
No, the highest class royal suite room →

153
00:16:29,155 --> 00:16:31,591
It is in use.

154
00:16:31,658 --> 00:16:36,029
This person lives in a different world than we do →

155
00:16:36,096 --> 00:16:38,031
He's a special person.

156
00:16:38,098 --> 00:16:40,033
(Minseok) Ah, no... >> Everyone→

157
00:16:40,100 --> 00:16:42,035
Please do not be rude.

158
00:16:42,102 --> 00:16:44,037
(Minseok) Um... >> Well then, everyone →

159
00:16:44,104 --> 00:16:46,539
Thank you for your continued support today.

160
00:16:46,606 --> 00:16:48,608
(All) Thank you very much.

161
00:16:51,611 --> 00:16:55,048
(Minseok) That manager. >> No way.

162
00:16:55,115 --> 00:16:59,552
I'm really jealous of him being the deputy manager at such a young age hahaha...

163
00:16:59,619 --> 00:17:02,555
Until I got into this position →

164
00:17:02,622 --> 00:17:04,557
It took 30 years.

165
00:17:04,624 --> 00:17:06,559
Moreover, from the head office →

166
00:17:06,626 --> 00:17:10,063
I've been told that I don't have to give you any special duties.

167
00:17:10,130 --> 00:17:12,065
(Minseok) Huh? (Mizushima) At most→

168
00:17:12,132 --> 00:17:15,635
Please be quiet so as not to cause any problems.

169
00:17:17,637 --> 00:17:28,648
♪～

170
00:17:38,124 --> 00:17:40,627
(Staff) Welcome, I'll take your luggage.

171
00:17:45,131 --> 00:17:48,067
(Staff) Do you have any trouble? (Male) I'd like to go to the banquet hall.

172
00:17:48,134 --> 00:17:50,069
(Staff) This is it.

173
00:17:50,136 --> 00:17:52,071
(Female) Um... (Minseok) Yes.

174
00:17:52,138 --> 00:17:56,075
>>Which restaurant can I have breakfast at?

175
00:17:56,142 --> 00:17:59,078
(Minseok) Yes, please take the elevator on the left →

176
00:17:59,145 --> 00:18:01,080
It's on the second floor.

177
00:18:01,147 --> 00:18:03,583
When you arrive, it's immediately on the right.

178
00:18:03,650 --> 00:18:07,086
>> You are really good at Japanese.

179
00:18:07,153 --> 00:18:09,589
Did it come from Korea?

180
00:18:09,656 --> 00:18:12,092
(Minseok) Ah... yes.

181
00:18:12,158 --> 00:18:15,094
>> That's amazing, even though we're from different countries.

182
00:18:15,161 --> 00:18:17,096
I respect you.

183
00:18:17,163 --> 00:18:31,611
♪～

184
00:18:31,678 --> 00:18:34,113
(Momoko) No, no, you can't give it away like this. (Shopkeeper) It's okay, it's okay.

185
00:18:34,180 --> 00:18:36,115
(Momoko) Hey, I'm in trouble. (Shopkeeper) I want to.

186
00:18:36,182 --> 00:18:38,618
The only person who says it bothers me even though I'm getting extras is my teacher.

187
00:18:38,685 --> 00:18:41,621
You have a lot of kids to eat, right?

188
00:18:41,688 --> 00:18:44,123
(Momoko) That's true, but... (Shopkeeper) Just take it.

189
00:18:44,190 --> 00:18:46,125
Yes, welcome! It's cheap!

190
00:18:46,192 --> 00:18:48,628
(Momoko) Ah!

191
00:18:48,695 --> 00:18:51,631
(Minseok) Thank you for yesterday.

192
00:18:51,698 --> 00:18:53,199
(Momoko) No.

193
00:18:54,701 --> 00:18:56,636
Ah, wait a minute! thank you very much.

194
00:18:56,703 --> 00:18:58,137
>>Ah, see you later.

195
00:18:58,204 --> 00:19:00,140
(Momoko) Please show me the progress of that injury.

196
00:19:00,206 --> 00:19:02,141
(Minseok) Ah, no, no... it's okay now.

197
00:19:02,208 --> 00:19:04,143
(Momoko) Doesn't it still hurt? (Minseok) It's gotten better.

198
00:19:04,210 --> 00:19:05,879
(Momoko) Are you feeling better? (Minseok) Yes.

199
00:19:05,979 --> 00:19:06,613
(Momoko) Didn't you have a fever? (Minseok) No.

200
00:19:06,713 --> 00:19:09,649
Oops! (Momoko) Eh, why? I'm sorry.

201
00:19:09,716 --> 00:19:11,651
Wait a minute... (Minseok) Are you okay?

202
00:19:11,718 --> 00:19:14,654
(Shopkeeper) What happened? What happened? (Momoko) My bag was torn.

203
00:19:14,721 --> 00:19:17,223
Ah, thank you. I'm sorry.

204
00:19:19,225 --> 00:19:21,160
I'm sorry, but you're hurt.

205
00:19:21,227 --> 00:19:23,663
(Minseok) Ah, no.

206
00:19:23,730 --> 00:19:26,165
I bought quite a lot.

207
00:19:26,232 --> 00:19:28,668
(Momoko) Yes.

208
00:19:28,735 --> 00:19:30,670
Ah, that's not true. (Minseok) Huh?

209
00:19:30,737 --> 00:19:32,672
(Momoko) Don't eat all this by yourself.

210
00:19:32,739 --> 00:19:34,607
I'm not that gluttonous...

211
00:19:34,674 --> 00:19:36,609
(Minseok) A child with a hearty meal→

212
00:19:36,676 --> 00:19:39,112
You said you have a lot.

213
00:19:39,178 --> 00:19:42,115
(Momoko) Huh? (Minseok) Huh?

214
00:19:42,181 --> 00:19:44,117
(Momoko) I'm home!

215
00:19:44,183 --> 00:19:47,120
(Kazami) Ah, welcome back, welcome back~｡

216
00:19:47,186 --> 00:19:49,122
Welcome back Momo-chan. (Momoko) I'm home.

217
00:19:49,188 --> 00:19:51,124
>> Huh? (Momoko) Kim Min-seok.

218
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:53,626
She served as an interpreter for a Korean patient.

219
00:19:53,693 --> 00:19:57,630
(Kazami) Ah, ah, he's the one who helped people like an action star.

220
00:19:57,697 --> 00:19:59,132
(Minseok) Ah, no...｡

221
00:19:59,198 --> 00:20:01,134
>> I'm Kazami, the director here.

222
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:03,136
Because there's a lot of food.

223
00:20:03,202 --> 00:20:05,138
(Minseok) Huh? >> Please go eat too.

224
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:08,641
It's curry and rice! Yay! (Momoko) Please.

225
00:20:08,708 --> 00:20:10,643
(Minseok) Sorry.

226
00:20:10,710 --> 00:20:12,645
>> I'll eat it.

227
00:20:12,712 --> 00:20:15,148
(All) Itadakimasu.

228
00:20:15,214 --> 00:20:17,650
(Momoko) Sorry, we don't have enough adult chairs.

229
00:20:17,717 --> 00:20:20,153
(Minseok) Ah, no, not at all. (Mika) Ah, again.

230
00:20:20,219 --> 00:20:22,655
Momo-chan's curry ingredients are huge.

231
00:20:22,722 --> 00:20:25,158
(Momoko) Huh? (Kazami) It's certainly exciting.

232
00:20:25,224 --> 00:20:27,660
(Momoko) Was it too big...

233
00:20:27,727 --> 00:20:30,163
(Minseok) I like you. (Momoko) Huh?

234
00:20:30,229 --> 00:20:33,166
(Minseok) I like hearty cuisine.

235
00:20:33,232 --> 00:20:42,609
♪～

236
00:20:42,675 --> 00:20:45,612
(Minseok) Those kids...

237
00:20:45,678 --> 00:20:48,615
(Momoko) Ah, they're all kids from the neighborhood.

238
00:20:48,681 --> 00:20:51,117
Many children have busy parents.

239
00:20:51,184 --> 00:20:54,120
>> After all, food is delicious when everyone eats it together.

240
00:20:54,187 --> 00:20:55,622
(Child) Yeah.

241
00:20:55,688 --> 00:20:57,624
Delicious. Delicious.

242
00:20:57,690 --> 00:21:09,636
♪～

243
00:21:09,702 --> 00:21:11,638
(Sound of spilling tea) (Child) Ah, Momo-chan.

244
00:21:11,704 --> 00:21:13,640
I spilled some tea. (Momoko) Yes, yes, yes.

245
00:21:13,706 --> 00:21:15,642
>> Teacher's replacement! (Momoko) Okay, wait a minute.

246
00:21:15,708 --> 00:21:18,144
(Child) Refill! (Momoko) Yes, yes, yes.

247
00:21:18,211 --> 00:21:20,146
(Minseok) Please sit down. (Momoko) Yeah, but...

248
00:21:20,213 --> 00:21:22,215
(Minseok) Leave it to me.

249
00:21:25,718 --> 00:21:28,154
(Minseok) Thank you for waiting.

250
00:21:28,221 --> 00:21:30,657
How long should the rice be?

251
00:21:30,723 --> 00:21:32,659
>> Lots!

252
00:21:32,725 --> 00:21:34,661
(Minseok) That's cool.

253
00:21:37,163 --> 00:21:40,600
>> Cool, like a prince.

254
00:21:40,667 --> 00:21:42,602
Hey everyone, come here.

255
